Le Corbusier: Oeuvre Complete 8 Volumes
Publisher: Les Editions d'Architecture | 1970-4 | ISBN: N/A | French/English/German | PDF | 1708 pages | 520.81 Mb

Le Corbusier: Oeuvre Complete, 1910-29, 1929-34, 1934-38, 1938-46, 1946-52, 1952-57, 1957-65, and Volume 8: The Last Works.
This exceptional Complete Works edition documents the enormous spectrum in the oeuvre of one of the most influential architects of the 20th Century. Published between 1929 and 1970, in close collaboration with Le Corbusier himself, and frequently reprinted ever since, the eight volumes comprise an exhaustive and singular survey of his work. This boxed set will be the crown jewel in anyone's library of architecture books.
